        Curled in a ball, Diame shook from the sounds of the rumbling, yet not a scratch on her. She slowly and cautiously surveyed around her and met with the gaze of the Sea-Daemon in disbelief. What is happening to me? She shook her head in disbelief. If this be a nightmare, let me awaken! If this isn't real, release me from this horrifying sweven! She faced back to the sea monster, her eyes locked with it. Her red hair trailed behind her, shimmering in the faint glints of the undersea sun. She knew swimming away wasn't doing any good, and yet, the explosive force of daemonic lightning could do her no harm. Release me! She demanded with the will of her thoughts.
         You daresst challenge me?! The two glowing eyes flickered again, and the sea went white, then black, then the eyes of the daemon turned blacker than black. This held and the contrast went darker and darker compared to the eyes of the sea-serpent. I sshall pull you into nightmaress ssteeped in depthss of darknessss beyond imagess your life will ever ssee. With all growing darker, the dark jewel glints in its eyes began to change color in this contrast. As if hidden within the black of its eyes, two burning glints of glaring red fire revealed themselves within the sea-serpent's eyes. The two red flames grew bigger, a furnace of hatred building brighter within its skull. The two jeweled spheres of its eyes became a binary of fulminating red stars. The darkness of the ocean began to turn to a dark-red, the distance started to look like a sea of blood. 
         The glare from the face of this beast... the half burnt and exposed skull and flesh of the serpent-crocodile chilled Diame. This is a dream. A sweven that can do no more harm than astonishment. And only I should have the power to compel my thoughts! She watched as the sea became brighter with a red as dark as night stretching beyond the sea. The sun of light above her was radiating a zenith of energy, a pure-white-sphere in an ocean of scarlet. Now daemon, I command you in our lady Evaz'Sa's name, to name thyself!
        The sea daemon's eyes burned like two jewels of fire pulsing from its skull. It bared its burnt teeth and curled a twisted smile on its charred lips. The ocean was a soup of boiling blood that grew chokingly hot in an instant.
        Diame tried to continue waterbreathing, but as a fish above water, she panted for breath that would not fill her lungs. Her thoughts began to slip and escape her, though a last horrifying realization crept past her mind before it drowned. He cannot withstand me compelling him with our lady's name. He wishes to stop me from even dreaming I'm saying it to him. I can... not breathe.


        Xavier rolled on the floor, his body began to quake further with the darkness overtaking him, torturing him for his interference. Crimson droplets began filling the sphere of water and light imprisoning Diame. The drops spread in the churning and turned to a ball of black and rust. Diame's face grimaced as if choking before it was lost in the haze. The Paladin let out a shout as the darkness engulfed his light further, taking hold and agonizing the life from him.
        Madame Oakh clasped a hand around her mouth and shuddered. She let out a groan as if her heart fell to the floor. She felt Mirnada tug at her robe tighter in wide-eyed horror. What can I do? What can any of us do? She turned to Tavian with wordless pleading written on her face.
